1. Install RVM
$ curl -L get.rvm.io | bash -s stable  (this will take a while)

2. Install Ruby: ruby -v => 1.9.3
$ rvm reload
$ rvm install 1.9.3 (this will take a while)
$ rvm --default use 1.9.3

3. Download RubyGems

4. Goto rubygems folder and run:
$ ruby setup.rb

5. Or update RubyGems:
$ sudo gem update --system

6. Install Rails:
$ sudo gem install rails (optional arg --version 3.2
$ rails -v => Rails 3.2.x

7. Install AppDorm
$ git clone https://github.com/larryaasen/appdorm_rails.git
$ bundle update
$ rake db:setup
